Mavericks Take 2-0 Lead Over Lakers; Bulls Tie 1-1 With Hawks in Playoffs

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-05-05T05:42:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/bulls-beat-hawks-to-tie-nba-playoff-series-at-1-1-lakers-face-mavericks.html
The Dallas Mavericks took a 2-0 lead
against the  Los Angeles Lakers  in the second round of the
National Basketball Association playoffs, while the Chicago
Bulls tied their series with the Atlanta Hawks at one game each.  Dirk Nowitzki scored 24 points as the Mavericks beat the
Lakers 93-81 at the Staples Center in  Los Angeles . Kobe Bryant
had 23 points for the Lakers, who travel to Dallas tomorrow in
search of their first win in the best-of-seven series.  At the United Center in Chicago,  Derrick Rose , who last
night accepted the trophy as the youngest Most Valuable Player
in NBA history, scored 25 points and Joakim Noah added 19 points
and 14 rebounds for the Bulls in their 86-73 win. Jeff Teague
led the Hawks with 21 points and Joe Johnson had 16.  The series shifts to Atlanta for a pair of contests
tomorrow and on May 8.  There are no playoff games scheduled today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
